    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">02</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Document Analysis</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Interpreting Texican Letters and Personal Accounts</h2><ul><li>Identify key themes: settlement struggles, cultural identity, and political tensions</li><li>Analyze language and tone for insight into Texican perspectives</li><li>Cross-reference with other sources for corroboration</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Personal letters reveal the lived experiences of Texicans, including their challenges and aspirations. Analyzing tone and language helps uncover underlying emotions and social dynamics. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A letter describing conflicts with Native tribes highlights both fear and negotiation efforts, illustrating complex frontier relations.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Select a letter excerpt and summarize the main concerns expressed by the author.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Taking emotional language at face value without considering broader context or possible exaggeration.</p></div></div>",
