    "eyebrow": "Terminology Timeline",
    "num": "07",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">07</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Terminology Timeline</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Mapping Terminology Changes to Historical Events</h2><ul><li>1820–1836: 'Texican' during Mexican Texas period</li><li>1836–1845: 'Texian' during Republic of Texas</li><li>Post-1845: 'Texan' after U.S. annexation</li><li>Terminology shifts coincide with sovereignty changes</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Creating a timeline helps visualize how terminology evolved alongside political transformations, reinforcing the link between identity and history. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Marking the Texas Revolution in 1836 as the pivot from 'Texican' to 'Texian'.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Construct a timeline including key events and terminology changes with brief explanations.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overlooking overlapping usage periods or regional variations in terminology.</p></div></div>",
