    "num": "09",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">09</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Practice Checkpoint</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Terminology Identification Exercise</h2><ul><li>Identify the correct term (Texican, Texian, Texan) for given historical scenarios</li><li>Explain reasoning based on political context and time period</li><li>Discuss implications for identity and allegiance</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Applying terminology knowledge to scenarios reinforces understanding of historical context and identity shifts. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Scenario: A settler in 1834 Mexican Texas is best described as a 'Texican'.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Classify five scenarios with dates and describe why each term fits or does not fit.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assigning terms without considering the specific historical timeframe or political status.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide33\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which of the following best defines a &#39;Texican&#39; during the early 19th century?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;A resident of Mexican Texas between 1820 and 1836 with cultural ties to Mexico and Spain&quot;,&quot;An Anglo-American settler arriving after Texas became a U.S. state&quot;,&quot;A Native American tribe living in Texas&quot;,&quot;A term used exclusively after the Texas Revolution&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:0,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;The term &#39;Texican&#39; specifically refers to residents of Mexican Texas during 1820–1836, reflecting their cultural background tied to Mexico and Spain.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Explain how the settlement patterns and lifestyle of the Texicans were influenced by land grant systems and frontier conditions.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;Response should describe the role of Mexican land grants and empresarios like Stephen F. Austin in shaping settlements, mention frontier challenges, and cultural influences on daily life.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;Texican settlements were largely shaped by Mexican land grant policies and empresarios such as Stephen F. Austin who brought settlers. The frontier conditions required adaptation to diverse cultural influences and challenges like Native American interactions.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;Land grants and empresarios influenced where Texicans settled and how they lived on the frontier.&quot;,&quot;Settlement patterns were shaped by Mexican policies and frontier dynamics affecting Texican lifestyle.&quot;,&quot;Texicans adapted their lifestyle due to land grants and the challenges of frontier life.&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
