    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">12</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Reflection</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Reflecting on Primary Sources and Terminology</h2><ul><li>How do primary sources deepen your understanding of Texican identity?</li><li>What challenges arise when interpreting historical terminology?</li><li>How can critical source analysis prevent misconceptions?</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Reflection consolidates learning by encouraging learners to connect source analysis and terminology with broader historical understanding. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Considering how a treaty’s language and the term 'Texican' together reveal political tensions.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Write a brief reflection on how terminology and primary sources shape your view of Texican history.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing terminology and sources as isolated facts rather than interconnected elements.</p></div></div>",
