    "num": "13",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">13</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Native American Influence</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Comanche Tribe: Military and Cultural Impact on Texicans</h2><ul><li>Comanche were dominant in Texas frontier during Texican period</li><li>Skilled horsemen and warriors influencing frontier security</li><li>Engaged in trade, raids, and negotiations with Texicans</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Comanche tribe played a critical role in shaping Texican frontier life through both conflict and cooperation. Their military prowess affected Texican settlement patterns and defense strategies, while trade relationships influenced cultural exchanges. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican settlers often negotiated peace treaties with Comanche leaders to secure safe passage and trade routes.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Consider how Comanche military strength might have influenced Texican decisions on settlement locations.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming Native tribes were only hostile; many interactions were complex and included trade and diplomacy.</p></div></div>",
