    "eyebrow": "Native American Influence",
    "num": "14",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">14</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Native American Influence</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Caddo Tribe: Cultural and Economic Interactions with Texicans</h2><ul><li>Caddo were primarily agricultural and settled in East Texas</li><li>Engaged in trade networks with Texicans and other tribes</li><li>Shared cultural practices influencing Texican frontier life</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Caddo tribe’s settled agricultural lifestyle and trade networks contributed to cultural exchanges with Texicans, influencing local economies and social practices in East Texas. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican settlers adopted some Caddo agricultural techniques and participated in regional trade fairs.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify ways Caddo cultural practices might have been integrated into Texican daily life.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overlooking peaceful cultural exchanges by focusing only on conflict narratives.</p></div></div>",
