    "eyebrow": "Native American Interactions",
    "num": "15",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">15</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Native American Interactions</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican-Native Relations: Conflict and Cooperation</h2><ul><li>Texicans faced frequent raids and negotiated peace with tribes</li><li>Military alliances sometimes formed against common enemies</li><li>Cultural exchanges occurred despite frontier tensions</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican interactions with Native tribes were complex, involving cycles of conflict, negotiation, and cultural exchange that shaped frontier dynamics. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> During periods of increased raids, Texicans formed militias and negotiated treaties to reduce hostilities.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze how Texican strategies balanced military defense with diplomatic efforts.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing Native-Texican relations as static rather than fluid and situational.</p></div></div>",
