    "eyebrow": "Practice",
    "num": "21",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">21</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Practice</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Analyzing Primary Sources on Texican-Native Relations</h2><ul><li>Examine excerpts from treaties and letters between Texicans and Native tribes</li><li>Identify evidence of conflict, cooperation, and cultural exchange</li><li>Assess perspectives and biases in the documents</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Engaging with primary sources develops critical skills in interpreting historical evidence about Texican and Native American interactions. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A treaty excerpt reveals negotiated peace terms and mutual obligations between Texicans and Comanche leaders.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze a primary source excerpt to determine the nature of Texican-Native relations it reflects.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Taking documents at face value without considering context or bias.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide45\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which of the following best defines a &#39;Texican&#39; during the early 19th century?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;A resident of Mexican Texas between 1820 and 1836 with cultural ties to Mexico and Spain&quot;,&quot;An Anglo-American settler arriving after Texas became a U.S. state&quot;,&quot;A Native American tribe living in Texas&quot;,&quot;A term used exclusively after the Texas Revolution&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:0,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;The term &#39;Texican&#39; specifically refers to residents of Mexican Texas during 1820–1836, reflecting their cultural background tied to Mexico and Spain.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Explain how the settlement patterns and lifestyle of the Texicans were influenced by land grant systems and frontier conditions.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;Response should describe the role of Mexican land grants and empresarios like Stephen F. Austin in shaping settlements, mention frontier challenges, and cultural influences on daily life.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;Texican settlements were largely shaped by Mexican land grant policies and empresarios such as Stephen F. Austin who brought settlers. The frontier conditions required adaptation to diverse cultural influences and challenges like Native American interactions.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;Land grants and empresarios influenced where Texicans settled and how they lived on the frontier.&quot;,&quot;Settlement patterns were shaped by Mexican policies and frontier dynamics affecting Texican lifestyle.&quot;,&quot;Texicans adapted their lifestyle due to land grants and the challenges of frontier life.&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
