    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">22</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Practice</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Comparative Analysis: Texican vs. Texian Cultural Narratives</h2><ul><li>Compare primary and secondary accounts of Texican and Texian identities</li><li>Identify shifts in values, language, and political allegiance</li><li>Discuss how narratives reflect broader historical changes</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This exercise deepens understanding of identity evolution by contrasting Texican and Texian cultural narratives through source analysis. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican letters emphasize Mexican heritage, while Texian proclamations highlight independence and Anglo values.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Create a comparative chart summarizing key differences and continuities between Texican and Texian narratives.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overlooking the persistence of cultural elements across identity shifts.</p></div></div>",
