    "eyebrow": "Application",
    "num": "24",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">24</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Application</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Applying Texican Identity Concepts to Modern Texas Culture</h2><ul><li>Identify lasting influences of Texican culture in contemporary Texas</li><li>Analyze how historical identity shifts inform current cultural diversity</li><li>Consider Native American legacies in Texas today</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Applying historical concepts helps learners connect Texican identity evolution and Native influences to modern Texas cultural dynamics. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Modern Texas place names and festivals reflect Texican and Native heritage.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Research a Texas cultural tradition or place name and trace its Texican or Native origins.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring historical roots when examining contemporary culture.</p></div></div>",
