    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">27</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Critical Evaluation</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Workshop: Comparing Sources for Bias and Gaps</h2><ul><li>Identify author background and potential bias</li><li>Note missing perspectives or information</li><li>Develop strategies to corroborate and fill gaps</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Through active comparison of secondary and primary sources, learners practice detecting bias, recognizing gaps, and planning corroboration strategies (s2, s6, s7). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Analyze a secondary narrative on Texican-Native American relations alongside a primary treaty document to identify differing emphases.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> In groups, compare two sources on the same event and list biases, gaps, and corroboration needs.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Focusing only on content agreement without considering source origin or omissions.</p></div></div>",
