    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">28</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Critical Evaluation</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Recognizing Limitations of Historical Sources</h2><ul><li>Understand incomplete or lost records</li><li>Acknowledge cultural and linguistic barriers</li><li>Consider the impact of historical context on source creation</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Historical sources are often incomplete or shaped by the context in which they were created, affecting their reliability and completeness (s3, s4, s7). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s3\">[3]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Discuss how language differences between Spanish and English documents affect interpretation of Texican history.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify potential limitations in a given primary source and suggest ways to address them.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming historical records provide a full and unbiased account of events.</p></div></div>",
