    "num": "30",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">30</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Summary &amp; Integration</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texicans’ Role in Early Texas History</h2><ul><li>Mediators between Mexican authorities and Anglo settlers</li><li>Participants in conflicts with Native American tribes</li><li>Active agents in the Texas Revolution and state formation</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans played pivotal roles in shaping early Texas history through political, military, and cultural engagement (s7, s8, s9). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Describe a Texican leader’s role in negotiating peace with Native tribes and later involvement in the Texas Revolution.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Outline key Texican contributions to Texas independence and frontier security.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring Texican agency by viewing them only as passive subjects of larger forces.</p></div></div>",
