    "num": "31",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">31</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Summary &amp; Integration</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Terminology and Identity Evolution</h2><ul><li>Texican: Mexican-era residents of Texas (1820–1836)</li><li>Texian: Residents during the Republic of Texas period</li><li>Texan: Post-annexation identity under U.S. governance</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The terms Texican, Texian, and Texan reflect shifting political and cultural identities over time (s2, s7). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Trace how a family’s self-identification might change from Texican to Texan across decades.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Match historical events with corresponding terminology and explain significance.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Using terms interchangeably without regard to historical context.</p></div></div>",
