    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">32</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Summary &amp; Integration</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Integrating Native American Perspectives</h2><ul><li>Recognize Native tribes’ influence on Texican life</li><li>Understand conflicts and alliances with Comanche, Caddo, and others</li><li>Acknowledge underrepresentation in historical narratives</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Native American tribes significantly shaped Texican frontier dynamics, yet their perspectives are often marginalized (s8, s9). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Examine a treaty between Texicans and the Comanche to understand mutual interests and tensions.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify how Native American interactions influenced Texican settlement and security.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing Native Americans only as obstacles rather than active participants in history.</p></div></div>",
